reviews.text: First time to try this restaurant. Not much to impress expect this deep fried fish skin with salted egg yolks. Never seen this dish before from other dim sum restaurant. I like the combination of the salty egg yolks with crispy fish skin. No fishy taste at all. Downside is The price is higher in general. Also the quality of tea no good. Will give them a second visit if in the area... Hmmm ... maybe not because too many choices in this area.

Very traditional menu, I've tried to be adventurous and opted for sea cucumber and mallet. It was ok.....rest of the food was tasty, but nothing extraordinary. Big portions, so if you're not too hungry perhaps should consider sharing. Staff not too attentive, but ok
A convenient place near MTR station. Both services and food are excellent
The worstest dim sum restaurant I've ever been to, really the worst of worst, never come
Food is delicious, comes fast and looks amazing! Wish they'd come to Europe so I could stuff my face 'whenever' I want!

result.name: 嚐中菜坊

reviews.text: 食物錯

與朋友相聚的好地方。
由於在尖東地帶，平日晚市時段，這裡的顧客並不多，我們在沒有訂位的情況下，也輕易找到座位。
湯點方面我們點了花膠淮杞螺頭白肺湯，湯很清甜，但每人只分得一碗，價錢略貴。
餸菜方面，選擇選多，有不同種類的海鮮、齋菜和肉等，可樂叉燒肥瘦適中，肉質鮮嫩，但可樂球配搭在此，有點不倫不類；辣味手撕雞份量雖然足夠，但味道偏鹹，不推介；生炒骨則中規中矩，排骨的粉漿不厚，所以吃起來不會太油膩；六味齋菜煲十分惹味，令人忍不住多吃兩口飯；
飯口點了脆麻花，十元一碟，相當實惠；還有甜品綠豆沙贈送，為在炎熱的天氣的我們，下一下火。

First time to try this restaurant. Not much to impress expect this deep fried fish skin with salted egg yolks. Never seen this dish before from other dim sum restaurant. I like the combination of the salty egg yolks with crispy fish skin. No fishy taste at all. Downside is The price is higher in general. Also the quality of tea no good. Will give them a second visit if in the area... Hmmm ... maybe not because too many choices in this area.

香港ツアー自由行動時間にマッサージ店へ行く途中に入ったお店です。店の外にコースメニューが貼ってあり、3〜4名分とあり、店に入って店員さんに、こちらは2名でそんなの多く食べれないのでランチセット的なのあるかと尋ねると「飲茶やっているよ。食べたいのを注文票に記入してさ」と言うことで、ジャスミンティーを頼んで食べたいのを選びました。漢字より英語表記がありがたい笑。鉄板はShrimp(エビ)だと読み3品頼み全部当たりでした。2人で6品頼みました。どれも美味しく、香港で自分がレストランを選んで食べた初の外食は当たりで良い思い出となりました。
(2019-3-22)

Very traditional menu, I've tried to be adventurous and opted for sea cucumber and mallet. It was ok.....rest of the food was tasty, but nothing extraordinary. Big portions, so if you're not too hungry perhaps should consider sharing. Staff not too attentive, but ok
